snippet: Following two starts in which he gave up 12 total runs, Cubs pitcher Paul Maholm held the Los Angeles Dodgers to one run in six innings in a 5-4 victory.
abstract: MLB Roundup; Washington Nationals defeat Philadelphia Phillies, 4-3; other results noted.
lead_paragraph: Following two starts in which he gave up 12 total runs, Cubs pitcher Paul Maholm held the Los Angeles Dodgers to one run in six innings in a 5-4 victory.

headline.seo: Nationals Rally to Beat Phillies in 11 Innings
headline.main: Poor Start Forgotten for Cubs’ Maholm
headline.print_headline: Game-Ending Single in 11th Inning Caps’ Nationals Rally Over Phillies
